1
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:20,765
PREVIOUSLY ON "KODIAK"...

2
00:00:24,633 --> 00:00:26,232
GET DOWN, GET DOWN,
GET DOWN!

3
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:28,765
THE SEASON IS COMING TO AN END.

4
00:00:28,766 --> 00:00:30,326
THIS BEAR
IS TWICE AS AGGRESSIVE.

5
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:34,002
THESE BEARS EAT RED MEAT,
AND WE'RE RED MEAT.

6
00:00:34,003 --> 00:00:36,130
AND THE FAMILIES ON THE ISLAND

7
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:37,632
HAVE BEEN PUSHED
TO THEIR LIMITS.

8
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:38,832
I'M SORRY.

9
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,471
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
EVER IN MY LIFE

10
00:00:40,472 --> 00:00:41,726
I'VE HAD TO SIT DOWN
WITH MY DAD.

11
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:43,302
I NEARLY
GOT KILLED TODAY.

12
00:00:43,303 --> 00:00:45,030
SURE YOU STILL
WANT TO DO THIS?

13
00:00:45,033 --> 00:00:47,802
THE HOLLAND BOYS GET
THEIR FIRST TASTE OF GUIDING.

14
00:00:47,803 --> 00:00:50,130
He should be right on the edge
of that forest.

15
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,832
You got him now.

16
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:55,132
BUT AS THE SEASON WINDS
DOWN, THE PRESSURE RAMPS UP.

17
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:56,732
LATER, KYLE.

18
00:00:56,733 --> 00:00:58,473
EITHER YOU **** GET
IT WRAPPED AROUND THAT MOTOR,

19
00:00:58,474 --> 00:01:00,496
OR WE'RE GONNA RIP
THAT WHOLE **** DEAL OFF.

20
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:02,799
YEAH, I DON'T GIVE A ****
IF YOU GOT TO CHEW A TREE DOWN

21
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:04,199
WITH YOUR **** TEETH
TOMORROW.

22
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:05,999
YOU NEED TO GET
SOME ****DAMN WOOD IN HERE.

23
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,330
YOU'RE SURE
YOU WANT TO DO IT?

24
00:01:07,333 --> 00:01:09,433
'CAUSE ONCE YOU TAKE A LIFE,
YOU TAKE A LIFE.

25
00:01:10,533 --> 00:01:11,970
DO I WANT TO BECOME A GUIDE?

26
00:01:11,971 --> 00:01:14,696
SOMETIMES I THINK YES,
AND OTHER TIMES, NO.

27
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:16,330
MY GOD!

28
00:01:16,333 --> 00:01:18,999
THERE'S A **** WHALE
RIGHT THERE.

29
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,099
That bear saw us.

30
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:21,299
Get down, get down, get down!

31
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:24,130
OH! I'M JAMMED.

32
00:01:26,133 --> 00:01:29,132
- Captions by VITAC-

33
00:01:29,133 --> 00:01:32,173
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

34
00:02:00,666 --> 00:02:02,496
PUDDLES ARE FREEZING.

35
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:03,665
IT'S COLD.

36
00:02:03,666 --> 00:02:06,065
ICE ON THE BEACH THIS MORNING.

37
00:02:06,066 --> 00:02:08,365
WE GOT TO START
WINTERIZING THIS PLACE.

38
00:02:08,366 --> 00:02:11,696
WINTER IS COMING
TO KODIAK ISLAND, ALASKA.

39
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:13,530
BEAR SEASON IS OVER,

40
00:02:13,533 --> 00:02:15,573
AND ALL OF THE HUNTERS
HAVE LEFT THE CAMP.

41
00:02:15,574 --> 00:02:17,596
FROZEN SOLID.

42
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:18,868
THE WEATHER COULD GET BAD.

43
00:02:18,869 --> 00:02:20,165
IT COULD FREEZE UP IN HERE,

44
00:02:20,166 --> 00:02:21,926
AND I MIGHT NOT SEE THIS PLACE
FOR FOUR MONTHS.

45
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:25,773
BOB MAY AND HIS CREW HAVE
ONLY DAYS TO PREPARE THEIR LODGE

46
00:02:25,774 --> 00:02:29,426
BEFORE THE ENTIRE ISLAND
IS ENTOMBED IN SNOW AND ICE.

47
00:02:29,433 --> 00:02:31,899
FROM THIS DAY ON,

48
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:35,830
WE'RE GONNA LOSE RUNNING WATER
TO THE BUILDING AND EVERYTHING.

49
00:02:35,833 --> 00:02:40,565
THERE'S PLENTY OF RUNNING WATER,
YOU JUST GOT TO RUN AND GET IT.

50
00:02:40,566 --> 00:02:42,496
AND WHAT'S WORSE,

51
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,999
THE ISLAND'S NAMESAKE,
KODIAK BROWN BEARS,

52
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,130
ARE STILL
ON THE HUNT FOR RED MEAT

53
00:02:47,133 --> 00:02:49,465
AS THEY BULK UP FOR HIBERNATION.

54
00:02:49,466 --> 00:02:51,526
TROY.
YEAH?

55
00:02:51,533 --> 00:02:53,370
SEE WHAT THE BEAR DID?
OH **** YEAH.

56
00:02:53,371 --> 00:02:55,026
YEAH,
HE DIDN'T QUITE GET IN,

57
00:02:55,033 --> 00:02:56,903
BUT THEN
HE BROKE OUT THIS WINDOW,

58
00:02:56,904 --> 00:03:00,530
TRIED TO GET IN THERE,
AND THEN DECIDED BETTER OF IT,

59
00:03:00,533 --> 00:03:01,870
BUT WE GOT TO COVER IT UP.

60
00:03:01,871 --> 00:03:03,696
SEASON'S COMING TO AN END,

61
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:06,230
AND TROY AND KYLE
HAVE DONE A GREAT JOB.

62
00:03:06,233 --> 00:03:07,770
THEY OBVIOUSLY WANT
TO BE GUIDES,

63
00:03:07,771 --> 00:03:09,426
AND I'M STILL A LITTLE
ON THE FENCE,

64
00:03:09,433 --> 00:03:12,703
BUT THEY'RE STRONGER TOGETHER
THAN THEY ARE APART.

65
00:03:12,704 --> 00:03:15,365
WE GOT TO GET THIS PLACE
SHUT DOWN.

66
00:03:15,366 --> 00:03:17,796
HOW MANY MORE WINDOWS
DO WE GOT TO DO?

67
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,999
A LOT.
WINTER'S HERE.

68
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,199
GOT TO GET THIS DONE BEFORE
THERE'S THREE FEET OF SNOW.

69
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:24,299
BUT NEXT YEAR, HOPEFULLY,

70
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:25,599
I WON'T BE
AN APPRENTICE DOING IT.

71
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,600
THAT ONE'S IN.

72
00:03:26,601 --> 00:03:28,199
GO HANDLE
YOUR **** COMPASS.

73
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,899
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN.
ALL RIGHT.

74
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:31,230
THANKS, BUD.
YEP.

75
00:03:31,233 --> 00:03:32,302
I'M ABOUT TO BE A GUIDE -

76
00:03:32,303 --> 00:03:34,130
ME AND KYLE, YOU KNOW,
SIDE BY SIDE.

77
00:03:34,133 --> 00:03:35,670
WE'RE GONNA DO THIS TOGETHER.

78
00:03:35,671 --> 00:03:36,796
I FEEL LIKE, YOU KNOW,

79
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,230
WE'RE AT THE LIGHT
AT THE END OF THE TUNNEL.

80
00:03:38,233 --> 00:03:41,732
CUT THESE SLICES SO THIN
IT'S LIKE I'M MAKING PAPER.

81
00:03:41,733 --> 00:03:43,902
I KNOW IF TROY AND I GET
OUR SHOT AS GUIDES,

82
00:03:43,903 --> 00:03:46,968
WE ARE GONNA BE AS GOOD
AS BOB CUSACK, BOB MAY,

83
00:03:46,969 --> 00:03:48,926
AND MY DAD, ERNIE,
TAUGHT US TO BE.

84
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:50,273
AND THEY'LL MAKE UP
THEIR MINDS

85
00:03:50,274 --> 00:03:53,096
BEFORE WE CLOSE THIS CAMP
FOR THE WINTER.

86
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,030
WE BETTER HURRY.
THE TIDE'S FALLING.

87
00:03:55,033 --> 00:03:57,932
IF WE CAN GET THIS THING TOWED
A LITTLE WAY, THAT'D BE GOOD.

88
00:03:57,933 --> 00:03:59,103
COME ON, DOGS. OUT.

89
00:03:59,104 --> 00:04:00,730
COME ON, ABBY.

90
00:04:00,733 --> 00:04:03,432
I DON'T HAVE A LOT
OF REAL CLOSE FRIENDS,

91
00:04:03,433 --> 00:04:05,632
BUT THE FRIENDS I HAVE

92
00:04:05,633 --> 00:04:08,065
LIKE ERNIE AND BOB,
I CHERISH THEM.

93
00:04:08,066 --> 00:04:10,326
YEAH, LET'S TRY AND GET THIS UP
HERE JUST A LITTLE WAYS.

94
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,865
GET IT STARTED.

95
00:04:12,866 --> 00:04:14,896
TO BE A BEAR GUIDE HERE
ON KODIAK,

96
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:16,930
YOU BETTER KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

97
00:04:16,933 --> 00:04:18,602
AND WE'RE ALL
PRETTY DAMN GOOD AT IT.

98
00:04:18,603 --> 00:04:21,368
YOU KNOW, I MEAN,
WE'VE KNOWN EACH OTHER FOREVER.

99
00:04:21,369 --> 00:04:23,796
YOU CAN'T FIND BETTER PEOPLE.
THEY'RE AWESOME.

100
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,999
IT'S LIKE HAVING FAMILY HERE
ALL THE TIME.

101
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,399
PROBABLY WOULD'VE BEEN
A LITTLE EASIER

102
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,630
IF WE TOOK THE MOTOR OFF,
BUT...

103
00:04:28,633 --> 00:04:29,633
YEAH.

104
00:04:29,634 --> 00:04:31,302
...WE'LL LET THEM YOUNGINS
DO THAT.

105
00:04:31,303 --> 00:04:34,268
LISTEN, SO, HOW ARE KYLE
AND TROY DOING OUT THERE?

106
00:04:34,269 --> 00:04:35,326
WHAT DO YOU GUYS THINK?

107
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,902
ARE THEY READY
TO BECOME GUIDES?

108
00:04:36,903 --> 00:04:38,399
GOT A NEW YEAR COMING UP
NEXT YEAR.

109
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,970
I THINK
THEY'RE PRETTY GOOD.

110
00:04:39,971 --> 00:04:41,196
YEAH.

111
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,530
I THINK THEY'RE PICKING UP
THINGS PRETTY FAST.

112
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:44,870
THINK THEY NEED
MORE EXPERIENCE.

113
00:04:44,871 --> 00:04:46,796
IS THAT BECAUSE
THEY'RE YOUR KIDS?

114
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,130
PROBABLY.

115
00:04:48,133 --> 00:04:49,973
KYLE AND TROY WERE KIDS,
ALL THEY WANTED TO DO

116
00:04:49,974 --> 00:04:51,465
WAS BE LIKE DAD
AND BE A BEAR GUIDE.

117
00:04:51,466 --> 00:04:53,426
<i>YEAH, SEE YOU LATER, TROY.</i>
<i>GOOD LUCK HUNTING.</i>

118
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:54,602
THE SCARIEST THING -

119
00:04:54,603 --> 00:04:56,430
SCARIER THAN ANY BROWN BEAR
OR ANYTHING -

120
00:04:56,433 --> 00:04:57,870
IS LOSING ONE OF MY KIDS.

121
00:04:57,871 --> 00:05:00,196
EVERY TIME
YOU STEP INTO THESE WOODS,

122
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:03,299
THERE IS A PROBABILITY
THAT YOU'RE GONNA DIE.

123
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:06,499
THEY NEED TO...
BE TOUGHER.

124
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,199
WHY DON'T WE JUST SEND THEM OUT
WITH ROBERT,

125
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,268
HUNTING THAT DAMN ELK?

126
00:05:09,269 --> 00:05:11,196
SURE AS HELL WOULDN'T HURT
FOR THEM

127
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,830
TO SPEND A LITTLE MORE TIME

128
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:15,432
DOING SOME
OF THE NON-DANGEROUS GAME.

129
00:05:15,433 --> 00:05:18,102
YEAH, SOMETHING LIKE THAT -
I THINK THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

130
00:05:18,103 --> 00:05:20,199
IT'S BETTER THAN NOTHING.
IT'S MORE EXPERIENCE.

131
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,899
I CAN SEE THAT ERNIE
LOVES HIS BOYS AND THAT

132
00:05:22,900 --> 00:05:24,830
AND CONCERNED ABOUT THEM,
BUT JUST SEEMED

133
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:28,999
TO COME AROUND A LITTLE BIT,
YOU KNOW?

134
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,968
WELL, LET'S JUST PLAY
A LITTLE GAME HERE

135
00:05:30,969 --> 00:05:33,426
AND HAVE ROBERT BE THE CLIENT
AND THEY'RE THE GUIDES,

136
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:35,965
AND THEN AT THE END
OF THE HUNT,

137
00:05:35,966 --> 00:05:37,796
WE'LL HAVE ROBERT
ASSESS THEIR PERFORMANCE

138
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,170
AS IF HE WAS A CLIENT.

139
00:05:39,171 --> 00:05:40,926
I'D FEEL GOOD ABOUT IT.

140
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:42,532
LET'S FINISH GETTING
THIS THING UP

141
00:05:42,533 --> 00:05:43,533
SO WE CAN HAVE A BEER.

142
00:05:43,534 --> 00:05:45,865
SOUNDS GOOD.

143
00:05:45,866 --> 00:05:48,426
CRANK AWAY.

144
00:05:51,866 --> 00:05:53,965
COME HERE.

145
00:05:53,966 --> 00:05:56,165
PUT THIS BAD BOY ON.

146
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:58,396
WE'RE GONNA SEE IF YOU CAN
PACK OUT SOME MEAT.

147
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,799
WE'LL MAKE SURE
YOU'RE WORTHY.

148
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,065
NEW PACK?

149
00:06:01,066 --> 00:06:04,265
I'LL TEST THE STRUCTURAL
INTEGRITY OF THIS THING.

150
00:06:04,266 --> 00:06:06,326
THOUGHT WE WERE GONNA LOAD IT UP
WITH SOME WOOD OR SOMETHING.

151
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:07,870
NO, ME,
'CAUSE I'M ABOUT

152
00:06:07,871 --> 00:06:09,496
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA BE
PACKING OUT.

153
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,999
ALL RIGHT.
WHAT DO YOU WEIGH?

154
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,265
180.

155
00:06:12,266 --> 00:06:15,765
TROY AND I HAVE AN
OPPORTUNITY HERE TO TAKE ROB OUT

156
00:06:15,766 --> 00:06:19,326
AND GUIDE HIM ON AN ELK HUNT,
AND I AM BEYOND EXCITED.

157
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:20,999
WE BECOME ONE.

158
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,130
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

159
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:25,265
OKAY, YOU READY?

160
00:06:25,266 --> 00:06:27,396
YEAH, ARE YOU IN THERE?
I'M ALL ON THE PACK.

161
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,199
ALL RIGHT.
HOLD ON TIGHT.

162
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:31,968
MY FIRST DEAR HUNT,
I WAS PROBABLY 11 YEARS OLD.

163
00:06:31,969 --> 00:06:34,526
BOB BROUGHT ROBERT OUT,
MY DAD BROUGHT ME OUT,

164
00:06:34,533 --> 00:06:37,165
AND WE WERE KIDS
GOING OUT HUNTING,

165
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:39,196
NOT REALLY TAKING THINGS
THAT SERIOUS.

166
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:41,999
BUT, YOU KNOW, OUR DADS,
BOB AND ERNIE,

167
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:45,030
DEFINITELY PROBABLY KEPT
A WATCHFUL EYE ON US BACK THEN.

168
00:06:45,033 --> 00:06:47,602
BUT NOW, WE CAN GO OUT
AND HUNT ON OUR OWN.

169
00:06:47,603 --> 00:06:49,270
I GOTCHA.
YOU'RE IN THERE.

170
00:06:49,271 --> 00:06:52,365
BEAR SEASON'S OVER NOW,
AND MY DAD,

171
00:06:52,366 --> 00:06:55,396
HE ASKED ME TO GO ELK HUNTING
WITH KYLE AND TROY,

172
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:57,130
AND I'M GONNA PUT 'EM
TO THE TEST,

173
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:59,132
YOU KNOW, SEE WHAT THEY CAN DO
AND WHAT THEY CAN'T DO.

174
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:01,399
OKAY, SET ME DOWN.

175
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:03,199
YEP.

176
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:06,530
ALL RIGHT, I THINK
YOU'LL BE ABLE TO HANDLE IT.

177
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:08,673
YEAH,
YOU'RE NOT SO BAD.

178
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,699
JUST HOPE
EVERYTHING GOES ALL RIGHT

179
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:25,399
AND WE MAKE IT BACK SAFE.

180
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:28,570
BOYS HAVE BEEN WORKING
PRETTY HARD AROUND CAMP, YOU KNOW?

181
00:07:28,571 --> 00:07:31,226
AND I DON'T THINK
I HAVE A BETTER WAY

182
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:34,870
TO TEST THE METTLE OF THESE BOYS
OTHER THAN SENDING THEM OUT

183
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:37,065
ON AN ELK HUNT WITH ROBERT,
AND BESIDES THAT,

184
00:07:37,066 --> 00:07:38,996
WE CAN GET SOME MEAT
IN THE FREEZER, YOU KNOW?

185
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,665
GRAB ME SIX ROUNDS,
KYLE.

186
00:07:40,666 --> 00:07:42,426
THIS IS OUR CHANCE
TO PROVE OURSELVES

187
00:07:42,433 --> 00:07:43,903
THAT WE CAN ACTUALLY HANG
IN THIS BUSINESS.

188
00:07:43,904 --> 00:07:46,268
I'M A LITTLE BIT EXCITED,
A LITTLE BIT NERVOUS.

189
00:07:46,269 --> 00:07:48,565
I'M READY FOR THE CHALLENGE.
I'M READY TO STEP UP.

190
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:51,868
HEY, MOM. HOW ARE YOU?

191
00:07:51,869 --> 00:07:53,565
BEFORE HEADING OUT
ON THIS ELK HUNT,

192
00:07:53,566 --> 00:07:55,096
I DECIDED TO CHECK IN
WITH MY MOM

193
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,630
ON THE EMERGENCY
SATELLITE PHONE.

194
00:07:56,633 --> 00:07:58,799
YEAH, WHAT DID THEY SAY?

195
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,199
STARTING WHEN?

196
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:03,668
SHE TOLD ME THAT SOMEBODY TRYING
TO GET AHOLD OF ME,

197
00:08:03,669 --> 00:08:07,326
BEEN E-MAILING ME FOR THE LAST
- I DON'T KNOW - FEW WEEKS,

198
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:10,432
AND WONDERING IF I HAD FALLEN
OFF THE FACE OF THE EARTH,

199
00:08:10,433 --> 00:08:12,432
'CAUSE I HAVEN'T HAD
ANY CONTACT.

200
00:08:12,433 --> 00:08:19,732
AND I GUESS I HAVE
A JOB OFFER COACHING SOCCER.

201
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:23,899
EVERYTHING THAT I'VE WORKED FOR
ALMOST MY WHOLE LIFE

202
00:08:23,900 --> 00:08:26,630
PERSONALLY AND PROFESSIONALLY,
IN SOCCER,

203
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:29,202
KIND OF CULMINATING
IN THIS ONE OPPORTUNITY.

204
00:08:29,203 --> 00:08:31,330
BUT I ENJOY BEING OUT HERE
SO MUCH

205
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:33,532
WITH MY DAD AND MY BROTHER
THAT I...

206
00:08:33,533 --> 00:08:36,032
MAN.

207
00:08:36,033 --> 00:08:38,665
IT'S...

208
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:42,826
WELL, MY DAD AND MY BROTHER
WOULD BE PRETTY HEARTBROKEN

209
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:44,670
IF I WERE TO TAKE OFF,
AND, YEAH,

210
00:08:44,671 --> 00:08:46,826
I'M REALLY CONFLICTED
IN WHAT TO DO.

211
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:49,903
AND I NEED TO TAKE SOME TIME
TO THINK ABOUT IT.

212
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:51,465
AH.

213
00:08:51,466 --> 00:08:53,496
WAITING ON KYLE.

214
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,499
I KNOW THAT THERE'S,
WHAT, ABOUT TWO OR THREE BEAR

215
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:56,999
THAT ALWAYS HUNT
THAT HERD UP THERE,

216
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,999
ESPECIALLY WHEN THEY'RE OUT
ON STEEP CAPE.

217
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,099
YEAH.
SO...

218
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:02,399
THEY'RE GOING UP TO A PLACE

219
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,230
WHERE THE BEARS
FOLLOW THE ELK HERD,

220
00:09:04,233 --> 00:09:05,732
AND THAT'S WHAT THEY'RE EATING,

221
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:08,070
AND SO IT CAN BE
DANGEROUS BEAR-WISE,

222
00:09:08,071 --> 00:09:10,965
BE DANGEROUS WEATHER-WISE -
ALL KINDS OF THINGS

223
00:09:10,966 --> 00:09:13,326
THAT CAN HAPPEN
THAT ARE BAD MOSTLY.

224
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:14,765
YOU MADE IT.

225
00:09:14,766 --> 00:09:16,326
