IN THE DARK, WE'RE SCREWED.

460
00:22:02,671 --> 00:22:04,126
LET'S LEAVE
HALF THE MEAT UP HERE.

461
00:22:04,133 --> 00:22:05,802
HAVE TO COME BACK FOR IT
IN THE MORNING.

462
00:22:05,803 --> 00:22:08,699
IF THAT'S WHAT
YOU THINK IS BEST, ALL RIGHT.

463
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:11,630
IF WE LOSE HALF THE MEAT,

464
00:22:11,633 --> 00:22:13,932
WELL, THAT'S BETTER
THAN LOSING OUR LIVES.

465
00:22:13,933 --> 00:22:17,302
THE SAFER THING TO DO IS THROW
HALF THIS MEAT UP IN THE TREES.

466
00:22:17,303 --> 00:22:18,868
THAT WAY, IF WE DO
RUN INTO SOMETHING,

467
00:22:18,869 --> 00:22:21,526
WE'RE NOT OVERWEIGHTED
WITH SO MUCH WEIGHT.

468
00:22:24,433 --> 00:22:25,699
BLACK BEARS CAN CLIMB TREES,

469
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:27,630
BUT KODIAK BROWN BEAR,
THEY'RE JUST TOO DAMN BIG.

470
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:28,903
THEY CAN'T GET UP THOSE TREES.

471
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:36,899
YOU GOT THAT?

472
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:38,830
YEAH, JUST TIE IT OFF
RIGHT THERE.

473
00:22:42,666 --> 00:22:47,165
LET'S KEEP EYES OUT
FOR BEARS.

474
00:22:47,166 --> 00:22:49,996
WHAT WAS THAT?

475
00:23:04,666 --> 00:23:09,165
LET'S KEEP EYES OUT
FOR BEARS.

476
00:23:09,166 --> 00:23:11,696
WHAT WAS THAT?

477
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:16,230
IT'S NOTHING.

478
00:23:16,233 --> 00:23:17,233
YOU GOT THAT?

479
00:23:17,234 --> 00:23:19,102
YEAH, JUST TIE IT OFF
RIGHT THERE.

480
00:23:19,103 --> 00:23:20,399
COME BACK IN THE MORNING

481
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:22,030
AND THERE'S A BEAR
UNDERNEATH THE TREE,

482
00:23:22,033 --> 00:23:24,699
IT'S A DANGEROUS SITUATION.

483
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:27,030
YOU KNOW, THAT'S HIS TERRITORY,
THAT'S HIS MEAT,

484
00:23:27,033 --> 00:23:28,170
HE'S DETERMINED THAT,

485
00:23:28,171 --> 00:23:30,065
AND HE'S GONNA DIE
TRYING TO PROTECT IT.

486
00:23:30,066 --> 00:23:32,326
ALL RIGHT, BOYS.

487
00:23:32,333 --> 00:23:34,632
HOPEFULLY, THAT MEAT'S
STILL THERE IN THE MORNING.

488
00:23:34,633 --> 00:23:36,402
WORKED TOO **** HARD

489
00:23:36,403 --> 00:23:37,970
TO GET IT THAT FAR
TO LOSE IT.

490
00:23:51,133 --> 00:23:56,832
IT'S TWO MORE RAVINES.
COME ON. JUST KEEP MOVING.

491
00:23:56,833 --> 00:23:59,302
THE DROPPING
TEMPERATURES OF LATE FALL

492
00:23:59,303 --> 00:24:01,730
TRIGGER A SURVIVAL INSTINCT
IN KODIAK BROWN BEARS

493
00:24:01,733 --> 00:24:03,873
THAT MAKES THEM RAVENOUS
FOR RED MEAT.

494
00:24:03,874 --> 00:24:06,265
THEY HUNT BOTH DAY AND NIGHT

495
00:24:06,266 --> 00:24:09,626
TO FATTEN THEMSELVES
FOR HIBERNATION.

496
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:12,032
WHEN A KODIAK BROWN BEAR
SMELLS BLOOD IN THE AIR,

497
00:24:12,033 --> 00:24:13,103
THEY'RE COMING FOR IT.

498
00:24:13,104 --> 00:24:15,630
THEY SMELL FRESH KILL,
THEY WANT IT.

499
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:21,730
I'LL FEEL BETTER
ONCE WE GET BACK INTO CAMP.

500
00:24:24,933 --> 00:24:28,465
OH! LAST HURRAH.

501
00:24:28,466 --> 00:24:31,626
WE MADE IT, BOYS.

502
00:24:31,633 --> 00:24:32,770
YES, WE DID.

503
00:24:32,771 --> 00:24:35,065
HEY, TROY,
WILL YOU HELP ME HANG THIS MEAT?

504
00:24:35,066 --> 00:24:36,696
THEN WE GOT TO
START A FIRE.

505
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:38,399
YOU KNOW, WE'RE PRETTY HAPPY
TO GET BACK INTO CAMP

506
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:39,899
WITHOUT ANY BEAR INCIDENTS,

507
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:42,068
BUT WE STILL HAVE
A LOT OF WORK TO DO.

508
00:24:42,069 --> 00:24:43,996
YOU CAN'T
LEAVE THAT MEAT SITTING DOWN.

509
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,268
ROBERT'S
GONNA HOP UP IN THE TREE

510
00:24:46,269 --> 00:24:49,796
AND THEN START HEAVING THOSE
120-PLUS-POUND HIND QUARTERS

511
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:51,599
30 YARDS UP JUST TO MAKE SURE

512
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,170
THAT THE BEARS
AREN'T GETTING INTO IT.

513
00:24:55,833 --> 00:24:57,403
WITH ALL OF THAT MEAT
UP IN THE TREE,

514
00:24:57,404 --> 00:24:58,665
WE'RE PRETTY MUCH BEAR BAIT.

515
00:24:58,666 --> 00:25:00,565
THERE'S EVERY SINGLE WORRY
GOING THROUGH MY HEAD.

516
00:25:00,566 --> 00:25:02,665
THIS IS NOT GOOD.

517
00:25:02,666 --> 00:25:04,796
ONE, TWO, THREE, GO.

518
00:25:08,633 --> 00:25:09,932
IS THAT THE LAST ONE?

519
00:25:09,933 --> 00:25:11,232
YEP, THAT'S IT.

520
00:25:11,233 --> 00:25:12,399
CALL IT GOOD.

521
00:25:17,566 --> 00:25:19,365
I'M **** EXHAUSTED.

522
00:25:19,366 --> 00:25:21,265
YOU'RE A DIFFICULT
FIRST CLIENT -

523
00:25:21,266 --> 00:25:25,526
TRYING TO REIN YOU IN
AND KEEP YOU CORRALLED,

524
00:25:25,533 --> 00:25:26,899
SO TO SPEAK.

525
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:30,030
I LOVE DOING THIS
ALMOST AS MUCH

526
00:25:30,033 --> 00:25:33,365
OR IF NOT MORE
THAN COACHING SOCCER.

527
00:25:33,366 --> 00:25:35,396
BEFORE NOW,
I WOULD'VE BEEN REALLY EXCITED

528
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:36,830
AND JUMPED AT THE OPPORTUNITY,

529
00:25:36,833 --> 00:25:39,032
AND RIGHT NOW I'M JUST HAVING
SECOND THOUGHTS.

530
00:25:39,033 --> 00:25:41,132
I DEFINITELY DON'T WANT TO
DISAPPOINT TROY.

531
00:25:41,133 --> 00:25:45,599
I KNOW THAT HE WOULD RELY ON
HAVING ME OUT HERE TO HELP HIM,

532
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:48,965
AND I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M GONNA DO,

533
00:25:48,966 --> 00:25:51,626
AND I'M REALLY TORN UP INSIDE.

534
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:55,132
BUT RIGHT NOW
ALL I'M THINKING IS,

535
00:25:55,133 --> 00:25:57,732
"WE'RE GONNA BE GOING OUT AGAIN
IN THE MORNING

536
00:25:57,733 --> 00:25:59,670
TO GO AND GET THAT SECOND LOAD."

537
00:25:59,671 --> 00:26:03,096
SO I NEED TO MAKE SURE THAT
MY HEAD'S IN THE RIGHT PLACE.

538
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:05,068
WHAT DO YOU THINK
THE CHANCES ARE

539
00:26:05,069 --> 00:26:08,196
THAT WE'RE GONNA COME ACROSS
A BEAR SITTING ON THAT MEAT?

540
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:11,130
THERE'S A PRETTY GOOD
CHANCE.

541
00:26:21,966 --> 00:26:23,996
ABBY, WANT TO GO DUCK HUNTING?

542
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:26,168
WANT TO GO DUCK HUNTING?
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

543
00:26:26,169 --> 00:26:30,065
WITH ALL THE CLIENTS
GONE, BOB, ERNIE, AND CUSACK

544
00:26:30,066 --> 00:26:32,365
HAVE TIME TO GET IN
ONE LAST HUNT

545
00:26:32,366 --> 00:26:34,296
BEFORE WINTER SHUTS THEM DOWN.

546
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:39,630
THIS TIME OF YEAR,

547
00:26:39,633 --> 00:26:41,970
IT'S TIME TO PUT SOME MEAT
IN THE FREEZER.

548
00:26:41,971 --> 00:26:43,396
THE BOYS ARE OUT HUNTING,

549
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:46,368
SO GO OUT WITH ERNIE AND CUSACK
AND SHOOT A FEW DUCKS.

550
00:26:46,369 --> 00:26:48,396
KIND OF LIKE OLD TIMES,
YOU KNOW?

551
00:26:50,266 --> 00:26:52,226
THAT'S A DOGGONE FINE DECOY

552
00:26:52,233 --> 00:26:55,232
THAT'S OUT THERE RIGHT NOW,
MISTER.

553
00:26:55,233 --> 00:26:58,473
NOW WE JUST GOT TO WAIT
FOR THE DUCKS.

554
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:05,099
- HERE'S A DUCK.
- HERE WE GO.

555
00:27:09,033 --> 00:27:10,699
ALL RIGHT, BOB.

556
00:27:10,700 --> 00:27:13,965
WONDER HOW THE BOYS
ARE DOING.

557
00:27:13,966 --> 00:27:17,196
TROY AND KYLE,
THEY'VE GOT THE BEST MENTORS

558
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:19,030
THAT YOU COULD EVER HAVE
IN GUIDING -

559
00:27:19,033 --> 00:27:21,265
BOB MAY AND BOB CUSACK.

560
00:27:21,266 --> 00:27:24,396
HERE THEY ARE COMING IN.

561
00:27:25,966 --> 00:27:27,796
YOU CAN'T MEET
A MORE INTERESTING PERSON

562
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:29,830
THAN BOB CUSACK.

563
00:27:29,833 --> 00:27:33,232
HIS GUIDE'S LICENSE
IS NUMBER 72, FOR GOD'S SAKE.

564
00:27:33,233 --> 00:27:37,402
I MEAN, HE WAS THE 72nd GUIDE
LICENSED IN THE STATE OF ALASKA.

565
00:27:37,403 --> 00:27:39,770
WHAT, THIS GUY
DID 45 YEARS UP HERE.

566
00:27:39,771 --> 00:27:43,726
HERE WE GO.
SOMETHING COMING UP.

567
00:27:45,066 --> 00:27:48,465
BOBBY MAY HAS MENTORED ME
IN THE GUIDE BUSINESS.

568
00:27:48,466 --> 00:27:50,996
I APPRENTICED UNDER HIM
FOR THREE YEARS HERE IN KODIAK,

569
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:52,468
AND THEN I STAYED
FOR ANOTHER 10.

570
00:27:52,469 --> 00:27:53,565
AND TO THE LADIES.

571
00:27:53,566 --> 00:27:55,465
THAT'S NOT ALL RIGHT
TO SAY THAT.

572
00:27:55,466 --> 00:27:56,965
COOKED
THIS WONDERFUL MEAL.

573
00:27:56,966 --> 00:27:58,896
I HAVE TO REALLY GIVE HIM CREDIT

574
00:27:58,900 --> 00:28:01,330
FOR A LOT OF THE SKILLS
THAT I HAVE NOW IN THE WOODS

575
00:28:01,333 --> 00:28:03,970
AND THE SKILLS THAT I HAVE,
YOU KNOW, BROWN BEAR HUNTING.

576
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:07,070
WELL, I HEAR A DUCK.
I HEAR A DUCK.

577
00:28:07,071 --> 00:28:08,965
HERE'S A DUCK.

578
00:28:08,966 --> 00:28:10,126
TAKE HIM.

579
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:16,465
TOUGH SHOT.

580
00:28:16,466 --> 00:28:20,165
I GOT MY GUIDE'S LICENSE
UNDER BOB.

581
00:28:20,166 --> 00:28:23,496
KYLE AND TROY ARE GOING THROUGH
THAT SAME APPRENTICESHIP.

582
00:28:23,500 --> 00:28:26,470
AS LONG AS YOU GOT ENOUGH DUCKS
TO EAT, I'LL BE HAPPY.

583
00:28:26,471 --> 00:28:31,265
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ROBERT'S
GONNA SAY ABOUT IT.

584
00:28:31,266 --> 00:28:33,966
WE'LL JUST HAVE TO SEE.

585
00:28:44,866 --> 00:28:47,065
KYLE, TROY, AND ROB
ARE TRAVERSING

586
00:28:47,066 --> 00:28:49,496
THE THREE MILES BACK
TO THE PLACE WHERE THEY LEFT

587
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:51,968
300 POUNDS OF ELK MEAT
HANGING IN A TREE.

588
00:28:51,969 --> 00:28:55,496
THEY MUST GET THE MEAT AND
HURRY TO THE RENDEZVOUS POINT

589
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:56,730
WITHIN TWO HOURS,

590
00:28:56,733 --> 00:28:59,703
OR RISK MISSING THEIR PLANE
BACK TO THE LODGE.

591
00:28:59,704 --> 00:29:02,799
JUST GOT TO KEEP MOVING.

592
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:04,299
FOR THE PAST EIGHT HOURS,

593
00:29:04,300 --> 00:29:05,468
THE SCENT OF THE HANGING MEAT

594
00:29:05,469 --> 00:29:07,626
COULD'VE DRAWN IN
EVERY BROWN BEAR

595
00:29:07,633 --> 00:29:09,932
WHO HAS BEEN STALKING
THE ELK HERDS IN THIS AREA.

596
00:29:09,933 --> 00:29:13,270
WE GOT A BIG TASK - WE GOT TO
GO BACK OUT IN THE FIELD,

597
00:29:13,271 --> 00:29:16,126
POTENTIALLY CHASE OFF A BEAR
FROM THE PRIZED MEAT

598
00:29:16,133 --> 00:29:18,373
THAT WE JUST WORKED SO HARD
GETTING.

599
00:29:35,633 --> 00:29:38,273
SCARY.

600
00:29:46,566 --> 00:29:47,665
ARE THOSE THEM -

601
00:29:47,666 --> 00:29:49,065
THESE TWO JUST RIGHT ABOVE
THE HORIZON?

602
00:29:49,066 --> 00:29:52,396
YEAH, I THINK IT IS.

603
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:54,630
THAT MEAT'S BEEN UP IN THAT TREE
ALL NIGHT.

604
00:29:54,633 --> 00:29:57,270
PLENTY OF TIME FOR A BEAR
TO COME AND THINK IT'S HIS.

605
00:29:57,271 --> 00:29:58,565
WE MAKE IT BACK TO THE MEAT.

606
00:29:58,566 --> 00:30:00,126
YOU KNOW, WE DON'T KNOW
IF THERE'S A BEAR THERE,

607
00:30:00,133 --> 00:30:01,899
SO WE GOT TO APPROACH IT
REALLY CALMLY.

608
00:30:01,900 --> 00:30:03,370
YOU KNOW, THERE COULD BE
A SLEEPING BEAR

609
00:30:03,371 --> 00:30:04,496
UNDERNEATH THE TREE.

610
00:30:12,133 --> 00:30:15,032
GUYS, LET'S MAKE A BUNCH
OF NOISE AS WE GET CLOSER.

611
00:30:15,033 --> 00:30:17,033
WE DON'T WANT TO SNEAK UP
ON A BEAR.

612
00:30:18,433 --> 00:30:20,465
HEY! HEY!

613
00:30:20,466 --> 00:30:22,626
HEY, BEAR!

614
00:30:22,633 --> 00:30:25,332
HEY! HEY!

615
00:30:25,333 --> 00:30:27,299
COO!

616
00:30:27,300 --> 00:30:28,499
NICE. THERE'S THE MEAT.

617
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:29,530
IT'S STILL HANGING.

618
00:30:29,533 --> 00:30:31,173
NO **** BEARS
GOT INTO IT.

619
00:30:31,174 --> 00:30:35,065
DROP YOUR PACKS,
TRY TO GET UP THERE.

620
00:30:35,066 --> 00:30:38,265
ALL RIGHT,
I'M GOING UP TO GET IT.

621
00:30:38,266 --> 00:30:40,496
COVER MY ASS.

622
00:30:40,500 --> 00:30:43,670
WATCH OUT FOR BEARS.

623
00:30:50,500 --> 00:30:52,200
HURRY UP, TROY.

624
00:30:56,900 --> 00:30:58,730
THERE YOU GO.

625
00:31:00,600 --> 00:31:03,099
THOSE BEARS CAN BE ULTRA-SILENT.
THEY'LL SIT THERE.

626
00:31:03,100 --> 00:31:05,530
THEY COULD AMBUSH YOU
IF THEY REALLY WANTED TO.

627
00:31:10,500 --> 00:31:11,630
GOOD TOSS.

628
00:31:13,166 --> 00:31:15,596
ALL RIGHT, I GOT IT.
LET'S GO.

629
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:28,430
LET'S DO IT.

630
00:31:28,433 --> 00:31:30,365
LET'S ROLL.

631
00:31:38,433 --> 00:31:40,902
IT'S NOT HEALTHY
TO BE OUT IN THE FIELD

632
00:31:40,903 --> 00:31:43,399
WITH BAIT ON YOUR BACK
IN BEAR COUNTRY.

633
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:45,030
THEY CAN SEE US,
AND WE CAN'T SEE THEM,

634
00:31:45,033 --> 00:31:46,803
SO THEY HAVE EVERY ADVANTAGE.

635
00:31:49,266 --> 00:31:51,626
THAT PLANE
HAS A SMALL WINDOW TO GET US,

636
00:31:51,633 --> 00:31:55,303
SO WE GOT TO HAUL ASS.

637
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:01,030
I'M DEFINITELY WORRIED
ABOUT GETTING LEFT ON THIS ISLAND.

638
00:32:01,033 --> 00:32:03,232
WE'RE BASICALLY
AT THE PILOT'S MERCY.

639
00:32:03,233 --> 00:32:04,473
WE'RE NOT CELEBRATING YET.

640
00:32:16,966 --> 00:32:18,596
SOMETIMES -
I KNOW THOSE FLOAT PILOTS -

641
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:20,830
THEY DON'T LIKE LANDING
IN WHITE-CAPPED WATERS,

642
00:32:20,833 --> 00:32:23,203
AND THERE'S SOME CAPS
THAT ARE CAPPING OUT THERE.

643
00:32:27,933 --> 00:32:29,132
CAN YOU HEAR IT?

644
00:32:29,133 --> 00:32:30,632
THERE'S THE PLANE.

645
00:32:30,633 --> 00:32:32,865
YEAH, HERE HE COMES.
THAT'S HIM.

646
00:32:32,866 --> 00:32:35,296
LET'S GO, BIG BOY.

647
00:32:36,766 --> 00:32:40,826
FEELS GREAT, YOU KNOW?
FINALLY, THE HUNT IS A SUCCESS.

648
00:32:40,833 --> 00:32:42,703
AND THE FACT THAT ME AND KYLE
MADE IT TOGETHER -

649
00:32:42,704 --> 00:32:43,865
I'M THRILLED.

650
00:32:43,866 --> 00:32:47,426
I'M PUMPED.
I'M EXHAUSTED, BUT I'M PUMPED.

651
00:32:47,433 --> 00:32:51,332
FINALLY. IT'S HERE.

652
00:32:51,333 --> 00:32:54,899
OH, MAN, THAT'S A SWEET SIGHT
RIGHT THERE.

653
00:32:54,900 --> 00:32:57,465
OH, BOY,
AM I GONNA BE HAPPY

654
00:32:57,466 --> 00:33:00,465
WHEN WE GET ALL THIS
BACK TO CAMP.

655
00:33:10,066 --> 00:33:13,065
I KNOW OUR DADS
ARE GONNA BE REALLY PROUD OF US

656
00:33:13,066 --> 00:33:15,326
THAT WE WERE ABLE TO
GET THIS ELK OUT SUCCESSFULLY -

657
00:33:15,333 --> 00:33:17,632
NO INJURIES, NO MISHAPS.

658
00:33:17,633 --> 00:33:18,803
NOW I NEED TO MAKE A DECISION

659
00:33:18,804 --> 00:33:22,165
WHETHER I'M GONNA TAKE
THE JOB COACHING OR STAY

660
00:33:22,166 --> 00:33:23,926
AND DO THE GUIDING BUSINESS
WITH MY BROTHER.

661
00:33:29,500 --> 00:33:31,400
HERE THEY COME.

662
00:33:34,166 --> 00:33:35,996
YEAH.
YOU DID.

663
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,399
HEY, BUD.
WHAT'S UP, DAD?

664
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,199
HOW'S IT GOING?
IT'S GOING GOOD.

665
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:41,099
HOW'D IT GO, ROBERT?
GOOD.

666
00:33:41,100 --> 00:33:43,130
DID YOU GET ANYTHING?

667
00:33:43,133 --> 00:33:44,603
GOT A COW, YEAH.
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

668
00:33:44,604 --> 00:33:46,965
OH, MAN. AWESOME!
THERE YOU GO.

669
00:33:46,966 --> 00:33:50,826
KYLE AND TROY ARE BACK,
AND THEY HAD A GREAT HUNT,

670
00:33:50,833 --> 00:33:53,370
BUT I'M MOST HAPPY
TO SEE THEM WALK OFF THE PLANE

671
00:33:53,371 --> 00:33:54,566
AND BE SAFE AND SOUND.

672
00:33:58,333 --> 00:34:00,299
WELL, GOOD JOB.

673
00:34:00,300 --> 00:34:02,170
ALL RIGHT,
I'M PROUD OF YOU GUYS. GOOD JOB.

674
00:34:02,171 --> 00:34:03,596
GOOD JOB, ROBERT.

675
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:06,268
I HOPE BECAUSE
OF THE SUCCESS WITH THE HUNT

676
00:34:06,269 --> 00:34:09,326
THAT THE BOBS AND MY DAD,
YOU KNOW, SEE THIS AND THEY SAY,

677
00:34:09,333 --> 00:34:11,902
"HO, DAMN. THOSE GUYS
CAN HOLD THEIR OWN, YOU KNOW?

678
00:34:11,903 --> 00:34:13,330
I'D HIRE THOSE GUYS ANY DAY."

679
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:27,030
WELL, THE ELK HUNT
WENT PRETTY GOOD.

680
00:34:27,033 --> 00:34:29,932
KYLE AND TROY ARE BACK,
AND THEY HAD A GREAT HUNT.

681
00:34:29,933 --> 00:34:33,003
NOW WE GOT TO SEE
WHAT ROBERT HAS TO SAY ABOUT IT.

682
00:34:33,004 --> 00:34:34,499
SO, HOW'D THE BOYS DO?

683
00:34:34,500 --> 00:34:37,230
THEY WERE ALL RIGHT.
THEY DID GOOD, YOU KNOW?

684
